# ── UPDATE 1: Extend Claim_CPCDissolvesSaleGap with patient-payer note ───────
DELETE {
  GRAPH ?g {
    narr:Claim_CPCDissolvesSaleGap skos:note ?oldNote .
  }
}
INSERT {
  GRAPH narr:Tx_20260430T120000Z {
    narr:Claim_CPCDissolvesSaleGap skos:note "CPC-on-goal-URL removes the upfront purchase decision that caused an engineering manager at the customer, the customer's chief architect, a collaborator, and a founder beta user to see value but not pay. Perspective-on-spec is the sales pitch itself; first payment arrives with first forward. This directly resolves the activation gap identified in Claim_UnderstandingNotEqualSale. Extended by a practitioner beta user Barber session (2026-04-30): the goal-driven payment primitive generalizes to multi-goal/multi-payer. Patient-as-goal-holder is a second payer mode — patient pays per vet when they consult against an existing perspective. Both modes coexist on the same platform: practitioner pays per click on their booking page for inbound discovery; patient pays per vet for outbound consultation. Same instrument, parameterized by who holds the goal." .
  }
}
WHERE {
  GRAPH ?g {
    narr:Claim_CPCDissolvesSaleGap skos:note ?oldNote .
  }
} ;

# ── UPDATE 2: Extend Narrative_MatchingSearchReframe with a practitioner beta user evidence ────
DELETE {
  GRAPH ?g {
    narr:Narrative_MatchingSearchReframe skos:note ?oldNote .
  }
}
INSERT {
  GRAPH narr:Tx_20260430T120000Z {
    narr:Narrative_MatchingSearchReframe skos:note "Scarlet reframed the product category: perspectives are an incredibly powerful search tool for a matching problem currently done very poorly — matching individuals to appropriate healthcare providers. Psychology Today is the negative example: property-based matching (specialties, modalities) that says nothing about how a practitioner actually thinks or what integrative care means to them. The reframe extends past alternative healthcare to therapists, psychiatrists, and traditional medicine. This does not replace the 'install expertise' mechanism — matching-search is what makes installation valuable when deployed externally. Extended by a practitioner beta user Barber session (2026-04-30): the practitioner marketplace use case concretizes this reframe — a practitioner beta user's PT meeting (two months to schedule) is the canonical example of the matching problem aswritten solves. The proposal artifact is the mechanism that resolves both patient illegibility and practitioner flattening simultaneously." .
  }
}
WHERE {
  GRAPH ?g {
    narr:Narrative_MatchingSearchReframe skos:note ?oldNote .
  }
} ;

# ── UPDATE 3: Extend Narrative_TwoSidedLegibilityProblem with proposal resolution
DELETE {
  GRAPH ?g {
    narr:Narrative_TwoSidedLegibilityProblem skos:note ?oldNote .
  }
}
INSERT {
  GRAPH narr:Tx_20260430T120000Z {
    narr:Narrative_TwoSidedLegibilityProblem skos:note "an early prospect's advertising problem (positioning around pain, two pieces of expertise, but a perspective behind that) is the inverse of Scarlet's patient problem (can't parse the medical system, can't tell which credentials are meaningful, can't find referrals). Patient-side illegibility and practitioner-side flattening are the same problem from opposite ends. aswritten makes the practitioner's perspective legible without forcing them to flatten. Extended by a practitioner beta user Barber session (2026-04-30): the proposal artifact is the concrete resolution mechanism — it describes the shape of the engagement and the practitioner's general methodology for cases like the patient's, without forcing the practitioner to flatten their methodology into marketing copy. The trust transfer mechanic (a practitioner beta user→patient trust already exists; a practitioner beta user→PT trust already exists; patient→PT trust is what the vet manufactures cheaply) is the structural insight that makes this resolution cheap to produce." .
  }
}
WHERE {
  GRAPH ?g {
    narr:Narrative_TwoSidedLegibilityProblem skos:note ?oldNote .
  }
} ;

# ── UPDATE 4: Extend Narrative_CompiledPerspectiveSourcePrivacy with healthcare application
DELETE {
  GRAPH ?g {
    narr:Narrative_CompiledPerspectiveSourcePrivacy skos:note ?oldNote .
  }
}
INSERT {
  GRAPH narr:Tx_20260430T120000Z {
    narr:Narrative_CompiledPerspectiveSourcePrivacy skos:note "The CTO's primary excitement was the ability to curate architectural knowledge abstracted from the codebase, allowing customer solution architects and partner AIs to query the knowledge base without accessing source code. This validates the compiled perspective / source privacy model as a core value proposition. Extended by a practitioner beta user Barber session (2026-04-30): the same mechanism applies to expertise services. Treatment cadence reasoning lives in clinical notes. Billing structure lives in operational documents. Handoff criteria live in supervisor letters. Visit pacing lives in case rationale notes. Methodology specificity (a practitioner beta user's jenga-block model) lives in the practitioner's head and unstructured material. None of this is on the practitioner's marketing site, and they don't want it to be. But the ideas in it are exactly what the patient needs to evaluate fit. aswritten ingests source-private content and cites the ideas without exposing the sources — the same mechanism that made the the enterprise customer CTO excited, applied to expertise services." .
  }
}
WHERE {
  GRAPH ?g {
    narr:Narrative_CompiledPerspectiveSourcePrivacy skos:note ?oldNote .
  }
} ;

